NOTICE: replace mpiexec with mpirun if that's what you use.

The commands above use mpiexec() from MPI.jl, which points at the bundled
MPICH_jll launcher. There are TWO different OpenMPI situations; check which one
you are in first:

    using MPI
    MPI.versioninfo()
    #  binary = OpenMPI_jll + a ~/.julia/artifacts/... path  -> CASE A (JLL)
    #  library = OpenMPI    + a system path (e.g. /opt/homebrew) -> CASE B (system)


#Parallel - CASE A: OpenMPI from the JLL (OpenMPI_jll)
#
# This is the common case if you switched MPI.jl away from MPICH_jll with
# MPIPreferences.use_jll_binary("OpenMPI_jll"). The launcher lives inside a
# Julia artifact and depends on other artifacts (e.g. Hwloc_jll's
# libhwloc.15.dylib). Calling a BARE `mpirun` from a shell fails with
#   dyld: Library not loaded: @rpath/libhwloc.15.dylib
# because the artifact library environment is only set up when the launcher is
# invoked THROUGH MPI.jl. So launch with the mpiexec() do-block (NOT bare
# mpirun, and NOT $(mpiexec()) interpolation - the do-block is what sets the
# environment that lets prte/mpirun find libhwloc):
using MPI
JULIA = Base.julia_cmd()
mpiexec() do exe
    run(`$exe -n 3 $JULIA --project=. -e 'using Jexpresso; Jexpresso.run_case("CompEuler", "thetaTracers")'`)
end
mpiexec() do exe
    run(`$exe -n 3 $JULIA --project=. -e 'using Jexpresso; Jexpresso.run_case("CompEuler", "3d")'`)
end
mpiexec() do exe
    run(`$exe -n 3 $JULIA --project=. -e 'using Jexpresso; Jexpresso.run_case("CompEuler", "city2d")'`)
end
mpiexec() do exe
    run(`$exe -n 3 $JULIA --project=. -e 'using Jexpresso; Jexpresso.run_case("CompEuler", "kelvinHelmholtzChan2022")'`)
end


#Parallel - CASE B: a real system OpenMPI (e.g. Homebrew, MacPorts, HPC module)
#
# ONE-TIME SETUP: bind MPI.jl to the system OpenMPI so the worker Julia
# processes load the same MPI mpirun launches them with. Find its lib dir with
#   ompi_info --path libdir        # e.g. /opt/homebrew/lib
# then (RESTART Julia afterwards):
